The governorship candidate of the All Progressives Congress (APC) in Zamfara state, Mukhtar Shehu Idris, has won his polling unit with a landslide victory. Idris polled 1,131 votes at the Army Barrack polling unit 014 in Tudun Wada area of Gusau local government area of the state. Our correspondent reports that the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) gubernatorial candidate, Bello Matawalle and his Accord party counterpart, Bala Bello, got one vote respectively. Zamfara APC candidate wins own polling unit Guber poll: Yobe APC candidate, Buni, wins polling unit APC leads in governorship, State Assembly polls in Oshodi